post caption:
Learning journeys can be filled with unexpected twists and turns, but they are always rewarding. Take Kishaâ€™s story.

Kisha paid her bills with a customer service call center gig on nights and weekends, but it wasnâ€™t what she imagined herself doing long-term. â€œI was tired of not living up to my potential,â€ she tells us.

The silver lining was that every shift wasnâ€™t exactly busy, so Kisha took to searching â€œcareers for introverts without a degreeâ€ in her downtime. She went down a major rabbit hole, but discovered how well web development paid, and although it was challenging â€” it was something she could learn without going back to school for a degree.

Kisha discovered Udemy while scrolling Facebook. She started taking courses in copywriting and social media marketing, before finding her way back to coding (more specifically email development). It wasnâ€™t long before she had freelance clients and was getting paid for the skills she had recently learned. Freelance work came with its own set of challenges, but Kisha used her experience to land a job at a marketing agency and other roles. Kisha estimates that she tripled the salary of her call center job in less than 2 years!

â€œIt filled me with confidence in myself. I had a lot of self-doubt before about achieving what I set out to do,â€ she recalls.

Today, Kisha has her own email marketing agency. She also volunteers her time teaching the skills sheâ€™s learned, speaks at tech conferences around the world, and is even developing a course on the Udemy platform focused on breaking into tech with a non-traditional background.

â€œI set out on this journey and now, I get to give back to other learners,â€ she beams.

Weâ€™re so proud of you Kisha and canâ€™t wait to check out your course!
